Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the error rate performance of FSO links with spatial diversity, which is a topic related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): FSO systems are a type of wireless communication technology, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.OH (Other Computer Science): This category includes papers that do not fit into any of the other sub-categories. While the paper is related to communication systems, it may not fit neatly into any specific sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses techniques to mitigate turbulence-induced fading, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.PF (Performance): The paper focuses on the performance of FSO systems over atmospheric turbulence channels, which is a topic related to performance evaluation.
